{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17646710","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17646710"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:34:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:34:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18201"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18201","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18201"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.11,0,0.7,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10915"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74127"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10915","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10915"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18201"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59618"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"524"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5220"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25375"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25378"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25504"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74127","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74127"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ENon-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) are commonly used for pain relief and inflammation reduction. However, they can lead to gastric ulceration due to their effect on the gastric mucosa.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following offers the most effective protection against this potential complication?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Histamine H2 receptor antagonists","Dietary modifications","Antacids","Proton pump inhibitors","Sucralfate"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProton pump inhibitors\u003C/strong\u003E are the most effective in protecting against gastric ulceration caused by NSAIDs. They work by significantly reducing gastric acid secretion, thereby decreasing the risk of ulcer formation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHistamine H2 receptor antagonists\u003C/strong\u003E - These also reduce gastric acid secretion but are less effective than proton pump inhibitors.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAntacids\u003C/strong\u003E - These neutralise existing stomach acid but do not prevent acid production.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESucralfate\u003C/strong\u003E - This forms a protective barrier over ulcers but does not prevent their formation.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDietary modifications\u003C/strong\u003E - While helpful in some cases, they do not provide significant protection against NSAID-induced ulcers.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) can cause gastric ulcers by inhibiting prostaglandin synthesis, which reduces the protective mucus layer in the stomach.","Proton pump inhibitors reduce gastric acid secretion, providing protection against NSAID-induced gastric ulcers.","Histamine H2 receptor antagonists can also reduce gastric acid secretion but are less effective than proton pump inhibitors."],"references":["Waller, D. G., \u0026 Hitchings, A. W. (2021). Medical Pharmacology and Therapeutics E-Book: Medical Pharmacology and Therapeutics E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Tashjian, A. H., \u0026 Armstrong, E. J. (2011). Principles of pharmacology: the pathophysiologic basis of drug therapy. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Queremel Milani DA, Davis DD. Pain Management Medications. 2023 Jul 3. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32809527","Carter GT, Duong V, Ho S, Ngo KC, Greer CL, Weeks DL. Side effects of commonly prescribed analgesic medications. Phys Med Rehabil Clin N Am. 2014 May;25(2):457-70. doi: 10.1016/j.pmr.2014.01.007. PMID: 24787343","Clarke K, Adler N, Agrawal D, Bhakta D, Sata SS, Singh S, Gupta A, Pahwa A, Pherson E, Sun A, Volpicelli F, Cho HJ. Indications for the Use of Proton Pump Inhibitors for Stress Ulcer Prophylaxis and Peptic Ulcer Bleeding in Hospitalized Patients. Am J Med. 2022 Mar;135(3):313-317. doi: 10.1016/j.amjmed.2021.09.010. Epub 2021 Oct 14. PMID: 34655535."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59618"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18201"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59618","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59618"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-24T19:13:13+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-24T19:13:35+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10915"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74127"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data